## Additional Terms for VIDHI Project

### Legal Disclaimer

VIDHI is an AI-powered legal assistance tool designed to provide general legal 
information and guidance. It is NOT a substitute for professional legal advice.

- This software provides general legal information only
- It does not constitute legal advice or create an attorney-client relationship
- Users should consult qualified legal professionals for specific legal matters
- The developers are not responsible for any legal consequences arising from use

### Data Privacy

- User conversations may be processed by AWS services
- No personal legal information is stored permanently without consent
- Users are responsible for not sharing sensitive personal information
- Audio recordings are processed for transcription only

### Indian Legal Context

This software is designed specifically for the Indian legal system and may not
be applicable to other jurisdictions. Legal information is based on Indian
constitutional law, statutes, and regulations current as of the development date.

### Government Scheme Information

Government scheme information is scraped from public sources and may not always
be current or complete. Users should verify scheme details from official
government sources before applying.

### AWS Services Usage

This software uses AWS services which have their own terms of service and
privacy policies. Users should review AWS terms when deploying this software.

### Contribution Guidelines

Contributors must ensure that:
- No copyrighted legal content is included without permission
- All legal information is factually accurate
- Code contributions follow security best practices
- No personal or sensitive data is committed to the repository

### Liability Limitation

The developers, contributors, and distributors of VIDHI shall not be liable for:
- Any legal advice or guidance provided by the AI system
- Inaccurate or outdated legal information
- Any legal consequences arising from use of this software
- Data loss, security breaches, or service interruptions
- Costs associated with AWS services or third-party integrations

### Compliance

Users deploying this software must ensure compliance with:
- Local data protection laws (including India's Personal Data Protection Act)
- AWS Acceptable Use Policy
- Applicable legal practice regulations
- Government scheme terms and conditions

### Support and Maintenance

This software is provided as-is. While the developers may provide updates and
bug fixes, there is no guarantee of ongoing support or maintenance.

